run docker build -t openvla .
Start a container, then copy files into it
This avoids bind mounting too.
to run docker start -ai openvla
Start a shell container:
    docker run -it --gpus all -p 9999:9999 --name openvla openvla bash

In another terminal, copy your files into the running container:
docker cp /home/dnguy439/Senior-Project/tcp/. tcp-dev:/app
Then inside the container:
cd /app
python main.py


docker run -u $(id -u):$(id -g) \
>   --runtime=nvidia \
>   -it \
>   --name openvla \
>   -v $HOME:$HOME \
>   -w $HOME \
>   tensorflow/tensorflow:latest-gpu \
>   bash

to go inside a docker that is running 
    docker exec -it tcp-dev bash
to reuse it run
    docker run tcp-dev-new